        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:43PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 343 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 13 miles north of Havre to near Chinook to 22 miles
southwest of Fort Belknap. Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Chinook, Harlem, Fort Belknap, Turner, Lohman, Hogeland, Cleveland,
and Zurich.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. An isolated
lightning strike cannot be ruled out with these showers.</instruction>
